dering\nthe three lowest redshifts. In our joint analysis of the matter PDF and matter\npower spectrum at three redshifts, the total neutrino mass is constrained to\nbetter than 0.01 eV with a total volume of 6 (Gpc/h)$^3$. We discuss how\ndensity-split statistics can be used to translate those encouraging results for\nthe matter PDF into realistic observables in galaxy surveys.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Nov 2019 19:00:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-13"}
